<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF4636539FE75CA0C" box="[310,446,1325,1351]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undefined-A">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF4636539FEB6CA0C" box="[310,381,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Ocotea</emphasis>
sp. A
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFC3FFEDF5246578FB72CEFA" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFC3FFEDF5246578FB72CEFA" blockId="39.[111,648,1388,1700]" lastBlockId="39.[676,1211,216,433]" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">
Represented by seven collections from the Sambirano-Manongarivo area.It has relatively large,glabrous leaves (
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF52265BFFF18CA8D" box="[119,211,1451,1478]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="10.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="8.0">8-13 cm</quantity>
) and long petioles (
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF4FC65BFFE31CA8D" box="[425,506,1451,1478]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3 cm</quantity>
). Venation is immersed,the upper leaf surface often shiny.Domatia are lacking.Vegetative buds are appressed pubescent. Infructescences are to 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF41E661EFE40C96E" box="[331,395,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="15.0">15 cm</quantity>
long, the cupules 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF768661EFD4FC96E" box="[573,644,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="1.5">1.5 cm</quantity>
in diameter and about 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF40E663EFE59C90E" box="[347,402,1578,1605]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
high without remnants of tepals. Fruits measure 2.5 × 
<quantity id="884D68DBFFC3FFEDF4ED665EFDCEC92F" box="[440,517,1610,1636]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" unit="cm" value="1.3">1.3 cm</quantity>
. Flowers are not known. 
<bibRefCitation id="2B24B8CFFFC3FFEDF5A9667EFE1BC9CF" author="KOSTERMANS A. J. G. H." box="[252,464,1641,1668]" firstAuthor="Kostermans" journalOrPublisher="Communication (Pengumuman) of the Forest Research Institute" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" pagination="1 - 44" part="57" refId="ref26822" refString="KOSTERMANS A. J. G. H. 1957. - Le genre Ocotea Aubl. (Lauracees) a Madagascar. Communication (Pengumuman) of the Forest Research Institute 57: 1 - 44." title="Le genre Ocotea Aubl. (Lauracees) a Madagascar" type="journal article" year="1957">Kostermans (1957)</bibRefCitation>
cited five of the collections as 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF456669EFEB5C9E8" authorityName="Kosterm. Kostermans" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Danguy" box="[259,382,1674,1700]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF456669EFEB5C9E8" box="[259,382,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; he did not see the sixth collection. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFC3FFEDF6E660CCFBE4CFB9" authorityName="Kosterm. Kostermans" authorityYear="1957" baseAuthorityName="Danguy" box="[947,1071,216,242]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="39" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF6E660CCFBE4CFB9" box="[947,1071,216,242]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">O. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in leaf shape and size, the shiny upper surface of the leaves, long petioles and the large cupules. The specimens are 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF7F36123FB7FCE1A" box="[678,1204,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Service Forestier 2567, 3792, 11084, 11501, 12281</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF7876143FC11CE3A" box="[722,986,342,369]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">Perrier de la Bâthie 10130</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFC3FFEDF6B26143FBE0CE3A" box="[999,1067,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="274">10131</emphasis>
, all in P; they were made in July (one collection), September (two coll.), October (two coll.) and November (one coll.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
